oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Virginia pine logs cut from the farm of Fred Waddell, are shown at the sawmill. Waddell's farm is located near Jacksboro, Tenn. in Campbell County.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Fred Waddell looks over some of the Virginia pine logs of the mill which helped him realize a $51.00 per acre net profit from his first weekend improvement cutting. He hired the cutting and milling, and sold the rough timber to a Knoxville lumber co.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: James M. Hendrix, SCS
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Forestry; Logs; Conservation of natural resources; Men; Lumber industry; Sawmills
